'''James Ellwood Jones House''' is a historic home located at [[Switchback, West Virginia|Switchback]], [[McDowell County, West Virginia]].  It is a two story, frame dwelling with an irregular plan. It features a classically detailed, pedimented porch, and stained glass windows.  Also on the property are a contributing swimming pool dated to the 1920s, a detached covered patio, a circular fountain, terraced garden, and greenhouse.  It was built for James Ellwood Jones, an influential leader in southern West Virginia's coal mining industry.<ref name="dhr">{{cite web|url=http://www.wvculture.org/shpo/nr/pdf/mcdowell/92000306.pdf|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: James Ellwood Jones House|date=January 1992|accessdate=2011-08-18 |author=Stacy Sone|publisher=State of West Virginia, West Virginia Division of Culture and History, Historic Preservation}}</ref>

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1992.<ref name="nris"/> 

